pr_review_comment_body:
I think our example code can become:
```python
Tracer.configure(settings={
    'PROCESSING_PIPELINE': [
        FilterRequestsOnUrl(r'http://test\.example\.com'),
    ],
})
```
just to make it simpler. Also, as we discussed, this is a WIP functionality so very likely `PROCESSING_PIPELINE` will be named differently.

Maybe this is already in your list of things to try, but: maybe use list comprehension? I played with it real quick and I think it's faster:

~~~python
    return [Synapse(i, segment)
            for i in xrange(len(segmentData.synapses))
            if not segmentData.synapses[i].destroyed]
~~~
